"{\"uid\": \"cyclingnews.com-races-olympic-games-2024-track-cycling-women-s-sprint-preview\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  Emma Finucane looks for gold in Olympic debut as reigning World Champion  When you purchase through links on our site, we may earn an affiliate commission.Here's how it works.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 177, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2, \"end\": 6, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tenille_Dashwood\", \"score\": 0.9998417097208697, \"rank\": 0.00015821473018392512, \"text\": \"Emma\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tenille_Dashwood\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tenille_Dashwood\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The latest race content, interviews, features, reviews and expert buying guides, direct to your inbox!\", \"from\": 179, \"to\": 281, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You are now subscribed  Your newsletter sign-up was successful  The track cycling events at theParis Olympicsbegin on Monday, August 5 and run all the way until Sunday, August 11, with the medals in the women's sprint being one of the final sets decided at the Saint-Quentin-en-Yvelines Velodrome outside Paris.\", \"from\": 283, \"to\": 594, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 588, \"end\": 593, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1202662485387758e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Qualifying will get underway for the 34 entrants on Friday, August 9, with the fastest 24 times in a 200m flying lap time trial heading into successive rounds of the well-known three-lap match sprints, where the field will be reduced down in the 1/32 and 1/16 finals and repechages.\", \"from\": 596, \"to\": 878, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the 1/32 phase, the top seeds will face the bottom seeds - first against 24th, second against 23rd and so on, before the losers play out the repechage races in threes to decide the 16 riders who go through.\", \"from\": 880, \"to\": 1089, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This process repeats in the 1/16 and 1/8 rounds.\", \"from\": 1090, \"to\": 1138, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The competition will resume on Saturday, August 10, for the 1/8 finals and repechages, where the field will be reduced to just the top eight riders to face off in four quarterfinals, with the best of three match sprint rounds resuming.\", \"from\": 1140, \"to\": 1375, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The semi-finals and medal finals will follow on the final day of track competition, where the gold medal and Olympic Champion will be decided after a thrilling afternoon of action on the Saint-Quentin-en-Yvelines boards.\", \"from\": 1377, \"to\": 1597, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The fight for gold should see the most powerful and explosive women's cyclists on the planet battle out for the top spot, with big stares on the start line, track stands, and should-to-shoulder racing all commonplace in one of Track's most exciting events.\", \"from\": 1599, \"to\": 1855, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Having been introduced to the Olympics as the first-ever women's Track cycling event in Seoul 1988, it'll be the 10th appearance of the individual sprint at the Games.\", \"from\": 1857, \"to\": 2024, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1945, \"end\": 1955, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9947939091003043, \"rank\": 0.005233335901753225, \"text\": \"Seoul 1988\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The latest race content, interviews, features, reviews and expert buying guides, direct to your inbox!\", \"from\": 2026, \"to\": 2128, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There have been eight different winners in the nine previous competitions, with the Atlanta 1996 and Sydney 200 champion F\\u00e9licia Ballanger (France) the only rider to win it back-to-back.\", \"from\": 2130, \"to\": 2316, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2214, \"end\": 2226, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1996_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.4782204584030665e-12, \"text\": \"Atlanta 1996\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1996_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1996_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2231, \"end\": 2237, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.609416479168181, \"rank\": 0.6409139324410615, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}, {\"begin\": 2251, \"end\": 2268, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/F\\u00e9licia_Ballanger\", \"score\": 0.9999999996002771, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"F\\u00e9licia Ballanger\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/F\\u00e9licia_Ballanger\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/F\\u00e9licia_Ballanger\"}, {\"begin\": 2270, \"end\": 2276, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9999251335971377, \"rank\": 5.2134001260045554e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kelsey Mitchell (Canada) returns as the defending Olympic champion, but without her two fellow podium sitters from Tokyo, as neither Olena Starikova (Ukraine) nor Lee Wai Sze is on the entries list.\", \"from\": 2318, \"to\": 2516, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2318, \"end\": 2333, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelsey_Mitchell_(basketball)\", \"score\": 0.9897172111837389, \"rank\": 0.010389610389608145, \"text\": \"Kelsey Mitchell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelsey_Mitchell_(basketball)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelsey_Mitchell_(basketball)\"}, {\"begin\": 2335, \"end\": 2341, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.6014335339817752, \"rank\": 0.6625680330486897, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2433, \"end\": 2438, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999947273893517, \"rank\": 5.2719710079486736e-06, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 2451, \"end\": 2456, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elena_of_Moldavia\", \"score\": 0.9999997711534241, \"rank\": 2.288372804706706e-07, \"text\": \"Olena\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elena_of_Moldavia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elena_of_Moldavia\"}, {\"begin\": 2468, \"end\": 2475, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8676481584147303, \"rank\": 0.1524237402045803, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2481, \"end\": 2492, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lee_Wai-sze\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lee Wai Sze\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lee_Wai-sze\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lee_Wai-sze\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While Mitchell will be in the running to be the first back-to-back winner since Ballanger, she's been knocked off of the top spot by a stacked German squad of sprint stars and a young British superstar.\", \"from\": 2518, \"to\": 2720, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2524, \"end\": 2532, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mitchell_family\", \"score\": 0.9951240967848931, \"rank\": 0.004899794084682982, \"text\": \"Mitchell\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mitchell_family\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mitchell_family\"}, {\"begin\": 2661, \"end\": 2667, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"score\": 0.9981246828258644, \"rank\": 0.0014935301905781401, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 2702, \"end\": 2709, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9452694825096043, \"rank\": 0.05787733185423865, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Emma Finucane (Great Britain) is the young Brit who heads into Paris 2024 as the reigning World Champion from her home championships in Glasgow last year.\", \"from\": 2722, \"to\": 2876, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2722, \"end\": 2726, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tenille_Dashwood\", \"score\": 0.9998417097208697, \"rank\": 0.00015821473018392512, \"text\": \"Emma\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tenille_Dashwood\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tenille_Dashwood\"}, {\"begin\": 2737, \"end\": 2750, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999336069, \"rank\": 5.2419752929213086e-11, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2785, \"end\": 2795, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.220899155671698e-23, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2812, \"end\": 2826, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_championship\", \"score\": 0.9581215360913629, \"rank\": 0.04370892649908325, \"text\": \"World Champion\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_championship\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_championship\"}, {\"begin\": 2858, \"end\": 2865, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow\", \"score\": 0.9976824308372382, \"rank\": 0.002322950429215111, \"text\": \"Glasgow\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Having added the European sprint title to her haul in Apeldoorn this past January, the Welsh rider arrives as the number 1 ranked rider and a huge hope for GB to win gold on Olympic debut.\", \"from\": 2877, \"to\": 3065, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2931, \"end\": 2940, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apeldoorn\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.9886039641450425e-18, \"text\": \"Apeldoorn\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apeldoorn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apeldoorn\"}, {\"begin\": 3033, \"end\": 3035, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9984426729296008, \"rank\": 0.0015597561208790004, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The German trio of medal contenders consists of former World Champions Lea Sophie Friedrich and Emma Hinze, alongside Pauline Grabosch, who has five times been team sprint World Champion on teams containing Hinze and Grabosch.\", \"from\": 3067, \"to\": 3293, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3071, \"end\": 3077, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"score\": 0.9981246828258644, \"rank\": 0.0014935301905781401, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 3138, \"end\": 3141, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lea_Salonga\", \"score\": 0.9999734462472958, \"rank\": 2.6554457847360123e-05, \"text\": \"Lea\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lea_Salonga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lea_Salonga\"}, {\"begin\": 3142, \"end\": 3148, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Scholl\", \"score\": 0.9624406904611694, \"rank\": 0.03630796487172908, \"text\": \"Sophie\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Scholl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Scholl\"}, {\"begin\": 3163, \"end\": 3173, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Hinze\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emma Hinze\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Hinze\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Hinze\"}, {\"begin\": 3185, \"end\": 3201, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pauline_Grabosch\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pauline Grabosch\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pauline_Grabosch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pauline_Grabosch\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Home French hopes will lie with 2022 sprint World Champion Mathilde Gros and former 500m time trial world champ Marie-Divine Kouam\\u00e9.\", \"from\": 3295, \"to\": 3427, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3300, \"end\": 3306, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999981155537646, \"rank\": 1.0163439004543713e-06, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3339, \"end\": 3353, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_championship\", \"score\": 0.9581215360913629, \"rank\": 0.04370892649908325, \"text\": \"World Champion\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_championship\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_championship\"}, {\"begin\": 3354, \"end\": 3367, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mathilde_Gros\", \"score\": 0.9999993327535274, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mathilde Gros\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mathilde_Gros\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mathilde_Gros\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Other nations who will be hopeful of a medal include New Zealand with reigning keirin World Champion Ellesse Andrews, who took bronze in the sprint event in Glasgow and Colombia with Martha Bayona, who is the fourth highest ranked sprinter in track sprinting.\", \"from\": 3429, \"to\": 3688, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3482, \"end\": 3493, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9327926690176024, \"rank\": 0.04870379531514221, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3508, \"end\": 3514, \"title\": \"http://dbped